The celebrated Athenais ⁷⁴ was educated by her father Leontius in the religion and sciences of the Greeks; and so advan- tageous was the opinion which the Athenian philosopher entertained of his contemporaries, that he divided his patrimony between his two sons, bequeathing to his daughter a small legacy of one hun- dred pieces of gold, in the lively confidence that her beauty and merit would be a sufficient portion.
